This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the use of machine learning applications in industry and proposes a novel Op fusion and code generation system for Tensorflow computations on GPUs. Additionally, the paper may also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it deals with image processing and optimizing computations on GPUs. The paper may also be relevant to cs.AR (Augmented Reality) as it discusses the performance improvements of latency-critical in-house applications. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it discusses the use of AI frameworks like Tensorflow.
